---

<section id="story" class="py-24 bg-cream">
  <div class="max-w-4xl mx-auto px-6">
    <span class="block text-xs uppercase tracking-widest text-spice-500 font-medium mb-4">
      Our Story
    </span>
    <h2 class="text-4xl md:text-5xl font-serif font-semibold mb-8 leading-tight">
      One mother. One recipe. <br />
      <span class="italic text-spice-700">Generations of memory.</span>
    </h2>

    <div class="prose prose-lg max-w-none text-ink/80 leading-relaxed space-y-6">
      <p>
        Every year, when the Alphonso and Raw Totapuri mangoes arrive at the
        market, a small kitchen in Bangalore comes alive. Glass jars are sun-dried.
        Mustard is roasted. Fenugreek is measured by feel — the way it has
        always been done.
      </p>
      <p>
        This is the pickle that friends and neighbors have asked for, year after
        year, for as long as anyone can remember. We finally decided it was time
        to share it beyond our family.
      </p>
      <p>
        <strong class="text-ink">Mother's Gold Spice</strong> is small-batch,
        preservative-free, and made with the same care as the jar that sits on
        our own kitchen shelf.
      </p>
    </div>

    <div class="mt-16 grid md:grid-cols-3 gap-8">
      <div class="border-l-2 border-mango-300 pl-5">
        <p class="font-serif text-2xl text-spice-700">Small batch</p>
        <p class="text-sm text-ink/60 mt-2">
          Every jar is hand-prepared. No factory. No assembly line.
        </p>
      </div>
      <div class="border-l-2 border-mango-300 pl-5">
        <p class="font-serif text-2xl text-spice-700">No preservatives</p>
        <p class="text-sm text-ink/60 mt-2">
          The salt, oil, and sun do all the preserving — the way it should be.
        </p>
      </div>
      <div class="border-l-2 border-mango-300 pl-5">
        <p class="font-serif text-2xl text-spice-700">Traditional recipe</p>
        <p class="text-sm text-ink/60 mt-2">
          Passed down, never written down. Made the way her mother taught her.
        </p>
      </div>
    </div>
  </div>
</section>
